headline.main: NEW-YORK CITY.; THE CANADA FORGERY. Investigation Concluded -- Arguments of Counsel.

docs.lead_paragraph: The judicial investigation respecting the alleged forgery of $5,000 drafts, and passage of them in Canada West, pending against, D. W. Van Aernam, P. W. Saw in, John W. Abell, and J. L White, was concluded on Thursday before Justice Stuart, at the Jefferson Police Court.

headline.main: The Senate and the Mortality at Sea.

docs.lead_paragraph: The resolution offered by Senator FISH to raise a Select Committee to inquire into and report upon the cause of the great illness and mortality on emigrant vessels, and what legislation, if any, may be needed, was, some three weeks since, adopted.
